# Backend (Python 3.10+ / FastAPI / SQLModel / Pydantic v2)

## Style
- Target Python 3.10+; use modern syntax (`X | Y` unions, `match` statements)
- Follow ruff rules already configured; run `ruff check --fix` before committing
- All functions must have return type annotations; use `-> None` explicitly
- Use `Annotated[T, Depends(...)]` for dependency injection, not default args

## FastAPI
- Group routes in `APIRouter`; prefix with resource name (`/patients`, `/encounters`)
- Use Pydantic v2 models for all request/response schemas (`model_config = ...`)
- Return explicit status codes: `status.HTTP_201_CREATED` for creates
- Raise `HTTPException` with meaningful `detail`; never return raw 500s
- Use `async def` for I/O-bound endpoints; plain `def` for CPU-bound

## SQLModel
- Table models: `class Foo(SQLModel, table=True)` — keep DB schema separate from API schemas
- Use `Session` via `Depends(get_session)` — never create sessions manually in routes
- Always define `id: int | None = Field(default=None, primary_key=True)`
- Alembic for all schema changes; never use `create_all` in production

## Pydantic
- Use `model_validator`, `field_validator` (v2 API); avoid legacy v1 validators
- Prefer `BaseModel` for API schemas, `SQLModel` only for DB tables
- Use `ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` when reading from ORM objects
